What a total load of ego-driven crap. 


Chris, if you&#39;re reading, may I suggest that you are the one who is falling victim to &quot;false&quot; communication? Or that your head is getting waaaay too big? Or if you already know that you&#39;re just in it for the cash, that you find another way to pay your bills?


You know, though, this same shit has happened to every group of paranormal researchers since the field began. I&#39;ve watched group after group come together and explode for thirty years because only the Chosen had the right to control the message, would broke no criticism of *any* of their own results *ever*, but had plenty of definitive pronouncements about everyone else&#39;s.


This is why I scoff at the idea of &quot;Harmony,&quot; with the capital H. I have seen the concept used by everyone from the Warrens in the 60s-70s to the Harsch-Fischbachs in the early 80s to Moon today trying to use this idea of being somehow chosen and sacred in order to get &quot;real&quot; messages from spirit. Harmony is a way to control who gets to play and IMHO, it&#39;s a load of nonsense.


Bruce, I have to tell you that the message you got the other day about us being all Kumbaya set my alarms off, perhaps innocently, but nonetheless. I&#39;ve found there is such a fine line between real peace between brothers working for the real common good and peace between brothers as a mechanism of control. Yes, we need to be at peace to work together. But that peace has to be an inclusive peace. It has to be a peace within one&#39;s self above all else. It needs to be a *fearless* interior peace, too. The Harmony is within, folks. It&#39;s not judging whether others have it or not before we let them play. It is pure, unadulterated *internal* knowledge about one&#39;s self. Judge not, lest ye be judged--remember that one?


HMO YMMV, toujours,


Ann



